So if you are friendly with the dog,

254
00:12:34.774 --> 00:12:37.580
you typically refer to it
as a "he" or "she".

255
00:12:37.610 --> 00:12:40.620
But if it's a dog that you don't know,

256
00:12:40.650 --> 00:12:44.860
maybe someone else's dog,
you refer to it as an "it".

257
00:12:44.890 --> 00:12:45.500
Okay?

258
00:12:45.530 --> 00:12:48.940
So in this case, we say,
"does my dog like to kiss me?"

259
00:12:48.970 --> 00:12:50.220
"Yes, it does."

260
00:12:50.250 --> 00:12:56.460
But we could have easily just have said,
"yes, he does", because it's my dog.

261
00:12:56.480 --> 00:12:58.100
Okay?
It's personal, right?

262
00:12:58.120 --> 00:13:00.900
So you're going to hear both,
just so you're aware of that.

263
00:13:00.930 --> 00:13:02.540
Okay?
Great!

264
00:13:02.570 --> 00:13:04.460
Now, awesome.
Get started now.

265
00:13:04.480 --> 00:13:06.540
Now, you have these
sentences top of mind.

266
00:13:06.560 --> 00:13:07.980
Go down to the normal version,

267
00:13:08.010 --> 00:13:11.820
listen to it two to three times
and let's get rocking and rolling.

268
00:13:11.850 --> 00:13:13.180
Then you go on to listen

269
00:13:13.210 --> 00:13:15.860
to the interactive version many,
many, many times.

270
00:13:15.890 --> 00:13:20.540
And remember to review your
phrases in the RAIO Application, right?

271
00:13:20.560 --> 00:13:24.100
And you can download the audios
and the transcripts on the orange button

272
00:13:24.130 --> 00:13:26.620
down here below if you
need to do that too.

273
00:13:26.640 --> 00:13:29.320
If you need to practice outside,
of the course, maybe if you don't have

274
00:13:29.320 --> 00:13:30.780
Internet connection or
something like that.

275
00:13:30.810 --> 00:13:33.000
If you're on a plane or somewhere where

276
00:13:33.000 --> 00:13:35.860
you have poor internet connection,
you can do that too.

277
00:13:35.880 --> 00:13:37.020
All right?
Awesome.

278
00:13:37.050 --> 00:13:38.900
Now remember, don't take notes, guys.

279
00:13:38.930 --> 00:13:41.460
I know that some

280
00:13:41.490 --> 00:13:44.300
of you guys have been
sitting here taking notes.

281
00:13:44.330 --> 00:13:46.500
Don't, don't take notes.

282
00:13:46.530 --> 00:13:50.340
Let the RAIO App do the work for you,
because all of these phrases are inside

283
00:13:50.370 --> 00:13:55.020
the RAIO App, and the RAIO App will help
you consume them using the technique

284
00:13:55.050 --> 00:14:00.100
of spaced repetition, which is way more
effective than taking and reading notes.

285
00:14:00.120 --> 00:14:01.740
Okay?
Please remember that.

286
00:14:01.760 --> 00:14:02.180
Awesome.

287
00:14:02.200 --> 00:14:04.360
Remember, you can go to the next section
when you're able to answer all

288
00:14:04.390 --> 00:14:07.900
the questions out loud, correctly
and without looking at the transcript.

289
00:14:07.920 --> 00:14:08.780
Right?
Perfect.

290
00:14:08.800 --> 00:14:09.820
And have some patience.

291
00:14:09.850 --> 00:14:12.340
Remember, input creates output.

292
00:14:12.370 --> 00:14:16.147
It's very probable that you say
to yourself,

293
00:14:16.347 --> 00:14:19.880
"Wow, Kale, I can actually
understand a lot of these things,

294
00:14:20.080 --> 00:14:20.940
but I can't speak."

295
00:14:20.970 --> 00:14:21.980
"It's so frustrating."

296
00:14:22.010 --> 00:14:23.180
"I can't speak."

297
00:14:23.210 --> 00:14:26.420
Yes, that is because it takes time.
Okay?

298
00:14:26.450 --> 00:14:31.860
Input creates output, but it takes time.
Okay?

299
00:14:31.890 --> 00:14:36.540
You will always understand more
than you're able to speak, okay?

300
00:14:36.570 --> 00:14:38.660
This process takes time,

301
00:14:38.690 --> 00:14:42.100
but the more input you get,
the more you get exposed to the language,

302
00:14:42.130 --> 00:14:46.340
the more the words and the grammar
structures will internalize in your brain.

303
00:14:46.370 --> 00:14:50.660
And then slowly but steadily, you will
start speaking more and writing more.

304
00:14:50.690 --> 00:14:53.500
That is just how language learning works.
Okay?

305
00:14:53.530 --> 00:14:57.380
But if you want to practice your
conversations anyways and practice

306
00:14:57.400 --> 00:15:01.020
speaking with other students, you can
do that in the RAIO Conversation Club.

307
00:15:01.040 --> 00:15:09.040
Practicing speaking and conversations,
you don't necessarily do that to improve

308
00:15:09.070 --> 00:15:13.780
your vocabulary or to improve your
speaking, but to improve your confidence,

309
00:15:13.810 --> 00:15:18.720
to improve the flow, to
get rid of fear and shame and things

310
00:15:18.750 --> 00:15:22.180
like that, which eventually
leads to better fluency.

311
00:15:22.200 --> 00:15:22.540
Right?

312
00:15:22.570 --> 00:15:26.380
So practicing speaking and practicing
conversations is still relevant,

313
00:15:26.410 --> 00:15:31.427
even though the main cause of language
learning is exposure to input.

314
00:15:31.627 --> 00:15:32.300
Consumption.

315
00:15:32.330 --> 00:15:33.340
Right?
Great.

316
00:15:33.360 --> 00:15:34.860
If you need a private coach

317
00:15:34.890 --> 00:15:38.580
to help accelerate your
learning and maybe if you have any

318
00:15:38.610 --> 00:15:43.460
specific needs, maybe you have a test
coming up, maybe you are a professional,

319
00:15:43.490 --> 00:15:44.140
I don't know,

320
00:15:44.170 --> 00:15:47.380
football player or swimmer,
and you need to learn vocabulary

321
00:15:47.410 --> 00:15:51.660
for that sport or that activity, well then
get a private coach who can help you

322
00:15:51.680 --> 00:15:54.300
accelerate the learning
in that particular field as well.

323
00:15:54.320 --> 00:15:56.140
We're here to help you.
We have the resources.

324
00:15:56.170 --> 00:15:57.980
It's all about you taking action.

325
00:15:58.010 --> 00:15:59.860
Okay? So that's it.

326
00:15:59.890 --> 00:16:01.970
Now, get started here down below

327
00:16:02.170 --> 00:16:05.500
with the normal version and
then the interactive version.

328
00:16:05.530 --> 00:16:09.220
And before we go on,
please repeat after me.

329
00:16:09.250 --> 00:16:16.120
"I'll become fluent in English."
"I'll never give up on my goal."

330
00:16:19.560 --> 00:16:20.820
Yes!
Awesome.

331
00:16:20.850 --> 00:16:22.300
Perfect.
Okay, great.

332
00:16:22.320 --> 00:16:23.520
I'll see you in the next one.
Bye.

